 {"target_molecule": "Arginine", "overall_strategy": "This network is a literature-guided hypothesis graph for prebiotic arginine centered on experimentally grounded precursor chemistry rather than a fully validated direct arginine synthesis. It uses hydrothermal generation of C1/C2 carbon feedstocks and keto-acid/amino-acid precursors, surface cyanide and ammonium-cyanide photochemistry to generate aminonitrile and guanidino-donor pools, and biochemical/prebiotic assembly steps to connect glutamate-like and ornithine-like intermediates to arginine. In line with the supplied literature, late-stage ornithine to arginine conversion is explicitly marked as speculative because direct prebiotic arginine synthesis is not experimentally established. The network emphasizes convergent hubs: HCN, formaldehyde, pyruvate, glutamate, and ornithine.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CO2", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "H2", "iupac_name": "molecular hydrogen", "common_name": "hydrogen", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2/h1H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "NH3", "iupac_name": "azane", "common_name": "ammonia", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "CH2O", "iupac_name": "methanal", "common_name": "formaldehyde", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O/c1-2/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "CHNO", "iupac_name": "methanamide", "common_name": "formamide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH3NO/c2-1-3/h1H,(H2,2,3)", "role": "intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_006", "formula": "CHN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "HCN", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CHN/c1-2/h1H", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_007", "formula": "C